Human associations and CSK resources contain a mix of salient but atypical assertions (lion attacks human), and typical but basic assertions (lion drinks water) [chalier2020joint]. To evaluate whether children's texts can help extract more typical assertions, we use PTLM prompting. Prompting is a standard procedure for extracting knowledge from masked-LMs [liu2021pre]. Given a relation of interest, e.g., ``LocatedAt'', one uses a generic textual pattern like ``{{2210.04530_FO0002||FO}}entity{{2210.04530_FO0003||FO}} can be found at [MASK]'', to obtain suggestions from an LM.